# 💰 Paisa — Smart Expense Tracker
## Complete Setup Guide (Novice-Friendly)

---

## What you need (just 3 things)
1. A Windows/Mac/Linux computer
2. Your Android phone + USB cable
3. ~20 minutes

---

## STEP 1 — Install tools on your computer

### 1A. Install Node.js
- Go to: https://nodejs.org
- Download the **LTS** version (green button)
- Install it (just click Next → Next → Install)
- To verify: open Command Prompt / Terminal and type `node --version` → should show a number

### 1B. Install Expo CLI
Open **Command Prompt** (Windows) or **Terminal** (Mac) and type:
```
npm install -g expo-cli eas-cli
```
Wait for it to finish (2-3 mins).

---

## STEP 2 — Set up the app

### 2A. Get the app files
- Copy the entire `paisa` folder to your Desktop (or anywhere you like)

### 2B. Install app dependencies
Open Command Prompt / Terminal, navigate to the paisa folder:
```
cd Desktop/paisa
npm install
```
Wait 3-5 minutes. You'll see lots of text — that's normal.

---

## STEP 3 — Install on your Android phone

### Option A: Test instantly with Expo Go (Easiest — 5 mins)
1. On your phone: Install **"Expo Go"** from Play Store
2. On your computer, in the paisa folder, run:
   ```
   npx expo start
   ```
3. A QR code appears in your terminal
4. Open Expo Go on your phone → Scan the QR code
5. App opens! 🎉

**Note:** In Expo Go, SMS auto-reading won't work (Android security restriction), but EVERYTHING ELSE works perfectly — you can add expenses manually, categorize, see charts, budgets, etc.

---

### Option B: Build a real APK file (Recommended — install permanently)

This builds a proper .apk file you install like any other app.

#### 1. Create a free Expo account
- Go to https://expo.dev → Sign Up (free)

#### 2. Log in on your computer
```
eas login
```

#### 3. Build the APK
```
cd Desktop/paisa
eas build --platform android --profile preview
```
- It will ask you to log in (use your expo.dev account)
- First time: answer "yes" to create a new project
- Build takes 10-15 minutes on Expo's free servers
- When done, it gives you a **download link**

#### 4. Install on your phone
- Download the .apk file to your phone
- On your phone: Settings → Security → Enable "Install from Unknown Sources" (or "Install Unknown Apps")
- Tap the downloaded .apk → Install
- Done! Paisa is installed as a real app ✅

---

## STEP 4 — Enable SMS Reading (for auto-import)

When you first open Paisa and tap "Sync SMS":
1. A permission popup will appear
2. Tap **"Allow"**
3. Done! Paisa will read your bank SMS messages

**Which messages does it read?**
Only messages from known bank senders (HDFC, SBI, ICICI, Axis, Kotak, Paytm, GPay, PhonePe, etc.)

---

## STEP 5 — Enable AI Categorization (Free!)

For smarter category detection:

1. Go to **More → Teach Paisa**
2. Tap **"How?"** to see instructions
3. Go to https://aistudio.google.com
4. Sign in with your Google account
5. Click "Get API Key" → "Create API Key"
6. Copy the key (starts with "AIza...")
7. Paste it in Paisa → tap Save

**That's it!** Google Gemini is FREE:
- 15 requests per minute
- 1 million tokens per day
- No credit card needed
- Way more than enough for personal use

---

## How to use Paisa

### Auto-import UPI/Card transactions:
1. Tap **"Sync SMS"** on the home screen
2. A bottom sheet pops up for each new transaction
3. Confirm the category (or mark as transfer)
4. Done! Takes 3 seconds per transaction

### Add cash transactions:
1. Tap the **+** button (bottom right)
2. Enter amount, merchant, category
3. Save

### Teach Paisa:
- When it gets a category wrong → tap the transaction → change category
- It learns and won't make the same mistake again
- Go to **More → Teach Paisa** to add rules and instructions

### Set budgets:
1. Go to **More → Budgets**
2. Tap any category
3. Enter monthly limit
4. Paisa will warn you when you're close

---

## FAQ

**Q: Is my data safe?**
A: Yes! Everything is stored ONLY on your phone. No servers, no cloud, no subscriptions.

**Q: Will it cost money?**
A: No. The app is free. Gemini API is free for personal use. Expo build is free.

**Q: SMS sync shows 0 transactions**
A: Make sure you allowed SMS permission. Also, the app only reads DEBIT messages from known bank senders.

**Q: The APK build failed**
A: Make sure you're logged in with `eas login`. Try again — sometimes there are temporary server issues.

**Q: Can I use it on iPhone?**
A: The app works on iPhone too but SMS reading is not available on iOS (Apple restriction). You'd add expenses manually or use the UPI app screenshot feature.

